Analysis and Insights :

Global Fungi-Basedbiopesticides Market

The fungi-basedbiopesticides market is expected to witness market growth at a rate of 15.20% in the forecast period of 2021 to 2028 and is expected to reach USD 6.20 billion by 2028. Data Bridge Market Research report on fungi-based biopesticides market provides analysis and insights regarding the various factors expected to be prevalent throughout the forecast period while providing their impacts on the marketâ€™s growth. The rise in the consciousness regarding the environment globally is escalating the growth of fungi-basedbiopesticides market.

Various fungal species are known to be utilized as agriculture microbials commercially including Aspergillus flavus, and Beauvaria bassiana, among others. Beauveria bassiana is one of these fungi that are highly used whitefly, aphids, thrips, psyllids, weevils and mealybugs. The microbial is generally applied in orchard crops such as fruits and berries, herbs and spices, vegetables, turf, forestry and ornamentals.

The rise in the acceptance of organic food among consumers across the globe acts as one of the major factors driving the growth of fungi-basedbiopesticides market. The use of synthetic chemicals can leading to pollution and contamination of the soil along with their harmful effects on the food chain and rise in awareness of residue-free food due to huge importance for biological products, accelerate the market growth. The high costs associated with the development of synthetic crop protection products and rise in adoption of fungi-basedbiopesticides by farmers to meet the standards prescribed by international exports, further influence the market. Additionally, increase in organic cultivation for fruits & vegetables and initiatives taken by government for emphasizing the use of integrated pest management and strategic developments such as expansions, new product launches, collaborations, and agreements positively affect the fungi-basedbiopesticides market. Furthermore, pest developing resistance to crop protection chemicals and advancements in microbial research by key players extend profitable opportunities to the market players in the forecast period of 2021 to 2028.

On the other hand, technological limitations for the use of biological products are expected to obstruct the market growth. The increase in the preference towards chemical pesticides among farmers in developing countries is projected to challenge the fungi-basedbiopesticides market in the forecast period of 2021 to 2028.

